# Building & Developing

The easiest way to build and develop Speedith is to install either
[Eclipse](http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/) or the
[NetBeans](http://netbeans.org/downloads/) IDEs:

Download one of the following:

* the Eclipse IDE for Java Developers, or
* the Java SE version of NetBeans.

# Dependencies

Right now Speedith depends on the following libraries:

* iCircles (Inductive Circles), found [here](http://git.gitorious.org/speedith/inductive_circles.git).
* Apache Commons CLI (Jakarta CLI), found [here](http://commons.apache.org/cli/).
* ANTLRv3, found [here](http://www.antlr.org/).
